The paper proposes a guided symbolic execution approach for data-flow testing, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The approach is implemented on KLEE, a symbolic execution engine, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the lack of effective tool support for data-flow testing, which could be related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of developing better tools and techniques.
